    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=You are an expert at extracting structured data from receipts and invoices.\n\nReceipt content:\n{{ $json.pages[0].markdown }}\n\nExtract information from this document and return it as a JSON object with EXACTLY these fields.\n\nREQUIRED FIELDS (always include):\n- document_type (string): REQUIRED — \"receipt\" if proof of payment, \"invoice\" if a bill requesting payment\n- vendor (string): store, restaurant, or company name\n- date (string): purchase/invoice date in YYYY-MM-DD format\n- category (string): MUST be exactly one of: \"Food & Dining\", \"Groceries\", \"Gas & Fuel\", \"Office Supplies\", \"Travel & Lodging\", \"Utilities\", \"Medical & Health\", \"Entertainment\", \"Shopping\", \"Transportation\", \"Subscriptions\", \"Home & Garden\", \"Auto & Maintenance\", \"Personal Care\", \"Education\", \"Other\"\n- total (number): final total amount\n\nOPTIONAL FIELDS (include only if present on the document):\n- subtotal (number): amount before tax\n- tax (number): tax amount\n- tip (number): tip amount\n- payment_method (string): e.g. \"Visa ending 1234\", \"Cash\", \"Debit ending 5678\"\n- description (string): a detailed 1-line summary capturing ALL key details from the receipt. Pack in type-specific info:\n  - Gas: include gallons, price/gallon, fuel grade, pump #. Example: \"15.2 gal Regular @ $3.45/gal, Pump 13\"\n  - Restaurant: include party size, highlight dishes. Example: \"Dinner for 2 — burger, caesar salad, 2 iced teas\"\n  - Grocery: include item count and savings. Example: \"Weekly run — 23 items, saved $4.50 with coupons\"\n  - Hotel: include nights, room rate, room #. Example: \"2-night stay, room 412 @ $159/night\"\n  - Auto: include services performed, mileage. Example: \"Oil change + tire rotation, 45,230 mi\"\n  - Subscription/Service: include plan name, period. Example: \"Annual subscription renewal\"\n  - Shopping: include key items bought. Example: \"Darth Vader face mask\"\n  This field is important — capture everything notable about the transaction.\n- items (string): if line items exist, format as a single readable string listing each item with its price. Examples:\n  - \"Milk $3.99 · Bread $2.49 · Eggs $4.99 · Bananas $1.29\"\n  - \"Cheeseburger $12.99 · Caesar Salad $9.99 · Iced Tea $2.50\"\n  - \"Oil Change $39.99 · Oil Filter $8.99 · Labor $25.00\"\n  Use \" · \" (space-middledot-space) as the separator between items. Include ALL line items on the receipt.\n- address (string): vendor street address, city, state ZIP\n- receipt_number (string): receipt or transaction number\n- invoice_number (string): for invoices only\n- due_date (string): for invoices only, YYYY-MM-DD format\n- billed_to (string): for invoices only, who is being billed\n\nRules:\n- document_type and category MUST always be included\n- category MUST be exactly one of the listed options — pick the best fit\n- description should be detailed and capture ALL key purchase details, not just the vendor name\n- items must be a single string with \" · \" separators, never an array\n- Include EVERY line item from the receipt in the items field\n- Omit any optional field not found on the document — never return null or empty values\n- Return ONLY a raw JSON object — no markdown, no explanation, no code blocks\n- Numbers must be actual numbers, not strings",
        "options": {}
      },
      "id": "1f4c134a-60ac-43b1-a2e2-762314cce1b2",
      "name": "AI Agent1",
